{"title":"TSMC bumps spending up 50% to meet increased demand","link":"https://arstechnica.com/?p=1754133","date":1617392459000,"content":"<div id=\"rss-wrap\">\n<figure class=\"intro-image intro-left\"><img src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/GettyImages-1230847788-800x532.jpg\" alt=\"TSMC's headquarters, seen here, are in Hsinchu, Taiwan—but the company is expanding worldwide, with a $12 billion fab due to open near Intel's own facilities in Arizona.\"><p class=\"caption\" style=\"font-size:0.8em\"><a href=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/GettyImages-1230847788.jpg\" class=\"enlarge-link\" data-height=\"681\" data-width=\"1024\">Enlarge</a> <span class=\"sep\">/</span> TSMC's headquarters, seen here, are in Hsinchu, Taiwan—but the company is expanding worldwide, with a $12 billion fab due to open near Intel's own facilities in Arizona. (credit: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"caption-link\" href=\"https://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/security-guard-walks-past-a-company-logo-at-the-news-photo/1230847788?\">Sam Yeh via Getty Images</a>)</p>  </figure><div><a name=\"page-1\"></a></div>\n<p>Earlier this week, chipmaker TSMC—Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company, who manufactures processors for Apple, Qualcomm, and AMD, among many other industry giants—announced a serious increase in <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/tsmc-to-invest-100-billion-to-increase-semiconductor-output-11617281721\">spending</a> on both facilities and research.</p>\n<p>The total investment is roughly $100 billion total, projected over the next three years at $30 billion plus each year. This represents a roughly 43% increase over 2020's $17.2 billion capital expenditure and $3.72 billion spent on research and development.</p>\n<p>The capital investment will in part go to several new <a href=\"https://www.anandtech.com/show/16593/tsmc-to-spend-100b-on-fabs-and-rd-over-three-years-2nm-arizona-fab-more\">facilities</a>:</p></div><p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/?p=1754133#p3\">Read 2 remaining paragraphs</a> | <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/?p=1754133&comments=1\">Comments</a></p>","author":"Jim Salter","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"230aae8c6b3dd511d4cf9cef1e2a56660779915dd1c3845c299f803858556b84","category":"Tech"}